## Hints for Future Agents
The final intended diff is only in vllm-tensorizer/Dockerfile. It should not include removal of ubuntu-toolchain-r apt sources, apt retry flags, or any other builder package management behavior. The simplified sed assumes the current Torch base arch list lacks 10.3/10.3a. If CI fails in apt before compilation, do not reintroduce the apt workaround unless the user explicitly approves widening the PR again. If CI reaches compilation, verify logs show 10.3a in TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST and nvcc flags with compute_103a,code=sm_103a. NVCC_WRAPPER_FILTER_CODES is a denylist; it should include plain sm_103/compute_103 but not sm_103a/compute_103a.

## Codebase Discoveries
The original Dockerfile style used a single compact GNU sed expression for arch conversion. This version preserves that style and adds only the minimal injection step needed for 10.3a.

